name: Timestamp
description: The Unix time stamp is a way to track time as a running total of seconds. This count starts at the Unix Epoch on January 1st, 1970 at UTC. e.g. 1632782567

name: WKT (Geometry data)
description: Well-known text (WKT) is a text markup language for representing vector geometry objects. A binary equivalent, known as well-known binary (WKB).

name: Character
description: It is used to store a single letter, digit, punctuation mark, symbol, or blank space. e.g. a, 1, #

name: String
description: It is a sequence of characters and the most commonly used data type to store text e.g. "this is a string", "so is this" .

name: List
description: Stores a number of elements in a specific order e.g. [1, 2, "array"] .

name: Integer
description: Numeric data without floating points (fractional components) e.g. 1, 22, 309 .

name: Dictionary
description: Used to store data in Key:Value pairs e.g. {"key" : "value"} .

name: Boolean
description: It represents the values true(1) and false(0) e.g. True, False, 1, 0 .
